# aws_glue_connection

Provides a Glue Connection resource.

## input variables

| Name | Description | Type | Default | Required |
|------|-------------|:----:|:-----:|:-----:|
|account_id|The id of AWS account.|string||Yes|
|region|This is the AWS region.|string|us-east-1|Yes|
|glue_connection_name|The name of the connection.|string|{{ name }}|No|
|glue_connection_catalog_id|The ID of the Data Catalog in which to create the connection. If none is supplied, the AWS account ID is used by default.|string||No|
|glue_connection_type|The type of the connection. Defaults to JBDC.|string|JBDC|No|
|glue_connection_description|Description of the connection.|string|Managed by TerraHub|No|
|glue_connection_properties_jdbc_connection_url|The url of the connection.|string||No|
|glue_connection_properties_password|The database password of the connetion.|string||No|
|glue_connection_properties_username|The database username of the connetion.|string||No|
|glue_connection_availability_zone|The availability zone of the connection. This field is redundant and implied by subnet_id, but is currently an api requirement.|string||No|
|glue_connection_security_group_id_list|The security group ID list used by the connection.|list|[]|No|
|glue_connection_subnet_id|The subnet ID used by the connection.|string||No|

## output parameters

| Name | Description | Type |
|------|-------------|:----:|
|id|Catalog ID and name of the connection|string|
|thub_id|Catalog ID and name of the connection|string|
